# rocket-r1 publishing policy — PUBLISH THE CODE, KEEP THE WEIGHTS AND DATA LOCAL.
#
# This file is the other half of the manifest we publish. The manifest claims
# open_source: true and ships an implementation_sha256 over the files listed in
# model/poker44_miner.py:SOURCE_FILES. That claim is only worth anything if those
# files are actually in the repo at the published commit — so every one of them is
# committed, and anyone can clone at repo_commit and recompute the digest.
#
# What stays private, and why it costs us nothing:
#   * trained weights (model/artifacts/*.pkl) — attested by manifest.artifact_sha256,
#     so the artifact is verifiable without being handed out. That is the edge: the
#     recipe is public, the fitted model is not.
#   * benchmark cache + live captures — data, not code; refetchable via autopilot.
#   * prose (README/docs) — not published; the code is the description.
#
# Secrets (.env: wallet, hotkey, ports) never go near a commit.

# --- secrets / operational config -------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- virtualenvs ------------------------------------------------------------
miner_env
miner_env/
.venv/
.venv312/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# --- trained artifacts: private; attested by manifest.artifact_sha256 -------
#
# model/artifacts/ is ignored WHOLE, meta.json included. An earlier revision
# un-ignored meta.json to publish it as a model card, which was wrong: autopilot
# rewrites it on every retrain that promotes, so a committed copy goes stale within a
# day and then contradicts the live manifest -- a card that misdescribes the running
# model is worse than no card, which is why d0's inherited one was dropped. The
# manifest IS the card: it carries model name/version/framework, repo+commit,
# implementation_sha256, artifact_sha256, the training-data statement and the
# attestations, and it is delivered to a validator on every single query.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.pkl
*.joblib
*.joblib.bak
*.npz
*.pt
*.pth
*.ckpt
*.h5
*.hdf5
*.onnx
*.pb
*.safetensors
*.bin
*.model
*.prefinal_bak
model/artifacts/
model/artifacts_backups/
model/artifacts_v1_backup/

# --- data: benchmark cache, live captures, diagnostics (never leave the box) -
model/data_cache/
model/live_capture/
model/external_data/
model/*.log
model/autopilot_history.jsonl
model/.retrain_in_progress
model/bakeoff_v3_results.txt
model/live_diag.json
model/live_payload_sample.json
_san_cache.npz
_san_cache_meta.json
catboost_info/
wandb/
hands_generator/human_hands/
hands_generator/evaluation_datas/
train_data/
retrain_data/
logs/
*.log

# --- prose: descriptions are not published; the code is the description ------
README.md
readme.md
docs/
*.md

# --- python -----------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
dist/
build/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/

# --- IDE / OS ---------------------------------------------------------------
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store
